<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-12-14T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-12-14T16:00:00-05:00" n="472" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d472">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/268: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Kaufman</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-12-14T16:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">December
                                            14, 1928—4 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>36. Your telegram No. 61, December 14, noon. Since the Conference
                                today by unanimous action (except Bolivia which was not present and
                                Paraguay which refrained from voting) offered its good offices, and
                                since I am Chairman of the Conference, I do not <pb facs="0821" n="693" xml:id="pg_693"/> desire to suggest anything which might
                                interfere with the action of the Conference or the acceptance of its
                                good offices which I am exceedingly anxious to have Bolivia
                                give.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>